data.title: Watch Movies Online
data.meta_description: Browse and watch award-winning movies now with AMC+. Stream online for free with your TV Provider. New on demand movies added every month.
data.text:
68 Kill

A robbery gone wrong sends a hapless guy (Matthew Gray Gubler) and his psychotic girlfriend on a seriously wild ride in this deranged, off-the-rails blast of no-holds-barred insanity.

Abandoned, The

Jason Patric co-stars in this terrifying plunge into a young woman's warped mind as she confronts demons both real and imagined from deep in the bowels of a decaying building.

Anesthesia

Kristen Stewart & Sam Waterston lead a great ensemble cast in this provocative drama about a shocking crime on a snowy New York night that changes one man's life forever.

Area 407

In this chilling, found footage horror film, the survivors of a plane crash find themselves trapped in a government testing area & hunted by mysterious pre-historic predators.

As Cool As I Am

Claire Danes & James Marsden star in this coming of age drama about a smart teenage girl who grows up in a small town with her self-centered parents.

ATM

A late-night stop at an ATM becomes a desperate fight for survival when three co-workers are trapped and terrorized by a mysterious hooded assailant.

The Atomic Submarine

SundanceTV Presents: Ships mysteriously disappear on route across the Arctic Sea, and a specially-equipped submarine is sent to investigate.

The Autopsy of Jane Doe

Coroners are mystified by an unidentified corpse until a series of terrifying events make it clear: Jane Doe may not be dead. Brian Cox, Emile Hirsch star in supernatural shocker.

Backcountry

In this terrifying thriller based on a true story, a young couple's romantic camping trip becomes a tale of survival as they face the dark side of nature: a man-eating bear.

Ballerina's Tale, A

A rare, behind-the-scenes look at the struggles and triumphs in the career of Misty Copeland, the first African-American named principal dancer of the prestigious American Ballet Theatre.

Band Aid

In a last-ditch effort to save their marriage a couple turns all their fights into song and starts a band with their neighbor. Zoe Lister-Jones, Adam Pally & Fred Armisen star.

Bare

An innocent young girl in a small Nevada town falls in love with a female drifter who leads her into a life of stripping, drugs, and psychedelic spiritual experiences.

Beneath

A deadly, supernatural force is unleashed underground with a crew of trapped coal miners and a female environmentalist in this creepy and claustrophobic horror thriller.

Best Offer, The

Geoffrey Rush is stunning as an eccentric art auctioneer obsessed with an heiress in this compelling mystery. Also stars Donald Sutherland.

Blood of the Vampire

In the late nineteenth century, the governor of a brutal prison institution, along with his crippled assistant, conducts research on the inmates.

Blue Room

Two adulterous lovers go from pillow talk to possible murder in this sexy, brain-teasing thriller directed by and starring Mathieu Amalric.

Born To Be Blue

Ethan Hawke lights up the screen as jazz legend and icon of cool, Chet Baker, whose comeback from heroin addiction is thrillingly told with wit, verve, and style to burn.

Bound To Vengeance

A captive woman escapes from her abductor - and turns the tables on him - in this edge-of-your-seat, bone-crunching revenge thriller.

Breaking the Girls

As the friendship between 2 beautiful women deepens, they embark on a murderous pact that escalates beyond their control in a twisted tale of seduction and betrayal.

Breaking Upwards

A witty romantic comedy about a young couple who try to re-energize their romance with a daring experiment: breaking up to stay together.

Brief Interviews with Hideous Men

Directed by John Krasinski and based on David Foster Wallace's best-selling book, this provocative and hilarious film explores sex and relationships. Co-starring Will Arnett.

The Brother From Another Planet

An alien from outer space lands in Harlem and is adopted by the local residents. This film is directed by John Sayles.

Burke & Hare

Simon Pegg & Andy Serkis in a wild, irreverent comedy based on the true exploits of two 19th century conmen who stumble upon a lucrative but disreputable new business.

Cabin Fever

A flesh-eating virus makes a meal of 5 teens on spring break in a remote wood cabin in this update of Eli Roth's classic gorefest, with all-new characters and all-new kills.

Cage Fighter, The

A mixed martial arts competitor risks everything-his family, his marriage, even his life-to keep fighting in this riveting, true-life tale of resilience.

Cam2Cam

A serial killer terrorizes a woman searching for the remains of her dead sister, trapping her in a web of horror and erotic intrigue.

Camp X-Ray

Kristen Stewart gives a stunning performance as a Guantanamo prison guard who forms an unlikely relationship with an inmate in this riveting psychological drama.

A Case of You

Justin Long and Evan Rachel Wood star in this romantic comedy about a man who creates a fake identity to win the love of a beautiful young woman.

Casino

Robert De Niro, Sharon Stone and Joe Pesci star in Martin Scorsese's riveting look at how blind ambition, white-hot passion and 24-karat greed toppled a Las Vegas casino empire.

Catcher Was a Spy, The

Paul Rudd stars in this true-life thriller about a Boston Red Sox catcher-turned-WWII spy tasked with assassinating a Nazi atomic scientist. With Jeff Daniels, Paul Giamatti.

Certain Women

Michelle Williams, Kristen Stewart, and Laura Dern lead a remarkable ensemble cast in this stunning portrait of three powerful and flawed women forging their own paths.

Chuck

Liev Schreiber, Naomi Watts, & Elisabeth Moss star in the incredible true story of a New Jersey liquor salesman who became the real-life inspiration for Rocky Balboa.

City of Gold

Jonathan Gold, the man who made food trucks and family restaurants foodie destinations, takes us on a mouth-watering odyssey in search of the next great culinary discovery.

Cold in July

In this action-packed pulp thriller starring Michael C. Hall, Sam Shepard and Don Johnson, a violent break-in triggers a journey deep into the bloody heart of Texas.

Contracted: Phase 2

A sexually transmitted virus is ravaging LA and turning lovers into flesh-eating zombies and one man is in a race against time to stop it.

The Crawling Eye

SundanceTV Presents: A series of decapitations on a Swiss mountainside appear to be connected to a mysterious radioactive cloud.

The Creation of the Humanoids

SundanceTV Presents: In a post holocaust society, robots take it on their own to help the dying human race by giving them android bodies.

The Cured

What happens when the undead return to life? Ellen Page stars in this smart, scary, and provocative look at a society attempting to heal in the wake of a zombie plague.

Curse of the Blood Ghouls

In an old castle in 19th century Austria, a newlywed couple is targeted by a savage vampire who is hellbent on destroying both their entire lives.

Daddy Longlegs

A bittersweet comedy about an unconventional father of two young boys hilariously trying to be a responsible parent - and failing every time.

Dancing in Jaffa

The power of dance unites sworn enemies as renowned ballroom dancer Pierre Dulaine brings together Israeli and Palestinian children by teaching them to dance together.

Dealt

Prepare to be inspired and amazed by Richard Turner, one of the world's most renowned card magicians, who met adversity head-on and refused to let his disability define him.

Decoy Bride, The

A Hollywood starlet's plans for a remote island wedding ceremony are complicated when the decoy bride she hires to distract the paparazzi falls for the real groom.

Den, The

A young woman witnesses a brutal murder in an online chat and is immersed in a nightmare in which she and her loved ones are targeted for a similarly grisly fate.

Dept. Q: A Conspiracy of Faith (Part 3)

Department Q goes on the hunt for a serial killer when a desperate message, written in blood by two children, is found 14 years after they were kidnapped.

Dept. Q: The Absent One (Part 2)

The brutal, 20-yr-old murder of a pair of twins is double the trouble for the detectives of Department Q in this 2nd installment in the blockbuster crime series.

Dept. Q: The Keeper of Lost Causes (Part 1)

A shocking cold case heats up when maverick detective Carl Morck is put on the job in the riveting first film in the Department Q series.

Desolation

A young mother, her best friend and son venture into the wilderness only to find themselves the hunted prey in a deranged killer's terrifying game.

Devil's Candy, The

An artist and his family think they've moved into the house of their dreams, but when he is possessed by a mysterious dark force the family must fight to save their souls.

Devil's Doorway, The

In 1960, two priests are sent to investigate a miracle in an Irish home for unwed mothers only to discover that one of the residents is possessed by the devil.

Devil's Pass

In this intense thriller, 5 young adventurers retrace the steps of a doomed group of hikers in pursuit of a legendary paranormal mystery.

Dheepan

Palme d'Or Winner. Gripping saga of three refugees who pose as a family to escape their war-torn home only to be caught up in gang violence in Paris.

Diary of a Nymphomaniac

In this scintillating drama, an insatiable lust for sexual pleasure drives Val, a young French girl, into a sordid life of prostitution and destruction.

Do I Sound Gay?

What a makes a voice "gay?" This witty, entertaining look at a controversial topic features candid interviews with Dan Savage, David Sedaris, George Takei, and Margaret Cho.

Don't Knock Twice

Knock once to wake her from her bed, twice to raise her from the dead. Katee Sackhoff is a mother fighting to save her daughter from demonic forces in this supernatural shocker.

Donnybrook

Jamie Bell is a veteran desperate to win or die trying in order to escape the ruthless criminal underworld and provide a better life for his family. Frank Grillo co-stars.

Duke of Burgundy, The

Two women take their carnal desires to the extreme in this kinky, deliciously twisted tale of sex and butterflies.

Elizabeth Harvest

A young wife is drawn into her husband's twisted secret world in this brain-bending plunge into our darkest desires.

Eloise's Lover

When sexy young Asia meets the passionate and fiery Eloise, they enter a steamy, forbidden relationship that causes a scandal.

Errors of the Human Body

Haunted by a personal loss, a brilliant geneticist working on a top-secret project unwittingly unleashes a new virus in this intense sci-fi thriller.

Espionage in Tangiers

A secret agent is assigned to capture a criminal gang that is threatening to destroy Earth with a death ray.

Exam

In this gripping thriller, eight strangers enter a ruthless competition to get the job of a lifetime, but the stakes soon become life or death.

Far From The Tree

Discover the courage of compassion through the eyes of parents journeying towards acceptance of their unique children. Based on The New York Times bestseller.

Female Brain, The

What makes a woman swipe right for Mr. Wrong? Sofía Vergara and Whitney Cummings star in this fresh, witty look at the science behind our romantic missteps.

A Few Good Men

A young Navy lawyer risks his career to uncover the truth during a military trial.

The Fifth Element

AMC Presents: In the colorful future, a cab driver unknowingly becomes the center of the search for a legendary cosmic weapon to keep Evil and Mr. Zorg at bay.

The Flesh Eaters

SundanceTV Presents: A group of young adults trapped on a desert island find the water inhabited by a violent form of flesh-eating organisms.

Following

In this brilliant suspense thriller from director Christopher Nolan, a voyeuristic writer enters a violent world of treachery and deceit when he crosses paths with a thief.

Frances Ha

Golden Globe nominee Greta Gerwig (Barbie) stars in this modern comic fable that explores New York, friendship, class, ambition, failure, and redemption. Written by Greta Gerwig and Noah Baumbach, who also directs.

Free the Nipple

In this empowering saga based on a true story, a group of fearless women fight for their right to go topless in New York City, as they smash taboos one bare breast at a time.

Free World, The

An Ex-Con attempts to start a new life only to be sucked back into the underworld in this romantic thriller. Elisabeth Moss, Octavia Spencer star.

Gates of Heaven

Errol Morris' first documentary examines the devotions, emotions and at times, obsessions exhibited by animal lovers when a pet cemetery is moved to a new location.

God's Pocket

Philip Seymour Hoffman and Christina Hendricks star in this deliciously twisted comedy about life and death on the mean streets of Philadelphia. Also stars John Turturro.

Good Time Max

Not exactly cut out for a desk job, Max converts his co-workers into meth-heads and party hounds in this hilarious comedy from the tripped-out mind of James Franco.

Goodbye To All That

In this smart, sexy comedy, a divorced dad (Paul Schneider) navigates the good, the bad, and the weird of the 30-something singles scene. Anna Camp and Heather Graham co-star.

The Great Outdoors

Dan Aykroyd and John Candy star in this comedy about an unannounced and unwelcome family of fun-loving misfits who converge upon a lakeside resort to join their relatives' vacation.

Haunt

When his family moves into a new home, a boy befriends a mysterious neighbor and unwittingly summons a demon in this chilling haunted house thriller. Co-starring Jacki Weaver.

Hell or High Water

A divorced father and his ex-con older brother resort to a desperate scheme in order to save their family's ranch in West Texas.

Hellion

Breaking Bad's Aaron Paul stars in this white knuckle thriller about a father and his out of control teenage son set against the high risk world of motocross.

House of Pleasures

A 16-year-old girl is thrust into the gritty, seductive world of the Apollonide bordello when she arrives to begin work at the famed Parisian brothel.

How to Make a Monster

SundanceTV Presents: When a master monster make-up artist is sacked by the new bosses of American International studios, he uses his creations to exact revenge.

Human Centipede 2: Full Sequence, The

A depraved mama's boy (Laurence R. Harvey) goes on a killing and collecting spree to recreate the experiment portrayed in "The Human Centipede (First Sequence)." 100% medically INaccurate.

Human Centipede 3: Final Sequence, The

500 prisoners, one body: the world's most deranged medical experiment reaches new heights in this final installment of the notoriously shocking trilogy. Stars Eric Roberts & Dieter Laser.

Human Centipede: First Sequence, The

A mad scientist achieves his dream of creating a human centipede by attaching three people together. Warning: This film contains extremely graphic violence and nudity.

I Am Not a Serial Killer

Christopher Lloyd stars in this thriller about a troubled teen who must hunt down a supernatural killer while battling his own inner demons. Based on Dan Wells' novel.

I Remember You

Two missing boys. One disturbing, decades-old secret. This hair-raising supernatural chiller is a powerful tale of life beyond death.

I, Daniel Blake

Cannes and BAFTA winner. A widowed carpenter and a single mother forge a touching friendship as they battle a callous welfare system in this powerful, urgent story.

In Her Skin

Two desperate parents take the law in their own hands after their daughter mysteriously disappears, in this gripping crime thriller based on a true story.

Into The Abyss

From legendary filmmaker Werner Herzog comes a riveting exploration of a horrible crime that probes the human psyche and explores why people kill.

Invasion of the Neptune Men

SundanceTV Presents: Clumsy invaders from Neptune are thwarted by hero Space Chief and a nondescript group of microshort-wearing Japanese kids.

An Invisible Sign

Jessica Alba captivates as a small-town teacher who finds the romance of her dreams in this touching, heart-warming fantasy.

A Kid Like Jake

Claire Danes, Jim Parsons, Priyanka Chopra and Octavia Spencer star in this funny and moving look at parents struggling with how to raise their nonconforming child.

Kill List

In this stunning, edge-of-your-seat thriller, Jay, a former hit-man, takes a final job for a mysterious client whose targets are tinged with the supernatural.

King Georges

In this foodie's delight, legendary chef Georges Perrier put Philly on the culinary map with his restaurant Le Bec-Fin -- but after 40 years can he keep his place at the top?

Kiss Her Goodbye

SundanceTV Presents: A man on the run with his beautiful, childlike sister finds love in a small Florida town.

Lianna

A wife and mother in search of meaning in her life finds love in the arms of another woman. This film is directed by John Sayles.

Loneliest Planet, The

Gael Garcia Bernal stars in this thriller about two lovers on an adventurous wilderness journey who face a life-changing event.

A Lonely Place To Die

A heart-stopping, action-packed thriller about 5 climbers thrust into a violent fight for their lives when they discover a girl buried alive in the wilderness.

Lucky Them

Toni Collette is a has-been rock journalist sent to hunt down a long-vanished local rock star (and old flame) in this edgy, moving comedy. Also stars Thomas Haden Church.

The Man Who Knew Infinity

Based on a true story, Jeremy Irons and Dev Patel star in this inspirational film about an obscure Indian mathematician whose groundbreaking theories changed mathematics forever.

Mary Magdalene

Rooney Mara & Joaquin Phoenix star in the moving story of a miraculous woman driven by her faith to follow Jesus. From award-winning director Garth Davis (Lion).

Mercy

A suave ladies' man (Scott Caan) finally meets his match, when the sexy female editor reviewing his novel, refuses to take the bait.

Myth of the American Sleepover

A gang of high-school students spend a decadent night full of sex, drugs and bad behavior.

Nightmare

In this horror film, a one night stand throws two film students into turmoil as they discover a mutual bloodlust that they cannot remember or contain.

Our Song

Three teenage girls face the challenges of growing up in a world filled with uncertainty, risk, and, ultimately hope.

Overbrook Brothers, The

After uncovering a long-buried secret on Christmas Eve, two brothers embark on a hilarious mad-cap cross-country journey to discover the surprising truth about their past.

Pack, The

Man's best friend becomes his worst nightmare when a horde of bloodthirsty wild dogs descends upon a family's farmhouse in a fang-bearing fight for survival.

Pact 2, The

When a series of brutal murders lead authorities to believe the Judas killer is back, Annie, (Caity Lotz), returns home for the final showdown.

Pact, The

In this gripping supernatural murder-mystery, a woman grieving her mother's death is haunted in her childhood home by the ghostly presence of a serial killer.

Passing Strange

Director Spike Lee's passionate adaptation of the thrilling Broadway musical about a young bohemian who experiences sex, drugs and rock and roll on his journey to selfhood.

Pelé

Discover the story of the greatest sports hero ever-how a kid from the slums of Brazil named Péle transformed soccer into the world's biggest sport. With Vincent D'Onofrio.

Personal Shopper

A young psychic is plunged into a dangerous game of cat and mouse when she makes contact with a sinister spirit. Kristen Stewart stars in this seductive thriller.

Plus One

When the party of the year is disrupted by a supernatural phenomenon, three friends must face a shocking new reality in order to survive the night.

Preppie Connection, The

In this wild but true story that rocked headlines in the 80s, a working-class teen gains acceptance from his prep school classmates by dealing cocaine from a Colombian cartel.

Prince of Space

When an alien force tries to invade Earth to steal a powerful new rocket fuel, a mysterious hero intervenes.

Pyewacket

When you're dealing with demons, be careful what you wish for... A teenager's death curse plunges her into an unholy occult nightmare.

Queen of Earth

Elisabeth Moss (Mad Men) stars as a desperate woman caught in a terrifying downward spiral in this heart-stopping psychological thriller. Also stars Patrick Fugit.

Quiet One, The

He was the bassist for The Rolling Stones and known as the "quiet one." Now, Bill Wyman speaks out about life in the world's greatest rock band through a tour of his personal archive.

Rebel in the Rye

Kevin Spacey & Nicholas Hoult star in the tale of the literary genius behind the masterpiece Catcher in the Rye and the mentor who helped change American culture forever.

Road Games

Nothing is what it seems in this terrifying thriller when a serial killer plays a game of cat and mouse with an unwitting hitchhiker who gets in the wrong car.

Roadracers, The

Banned from U.S. competition after causing a death, a race-car driver goes to Europe and dominates the tracks.

Robin Hood: Men in Tights

In preventing greedy Prince John and sinister Sheriff Rottingham from usurping power from an absent King Richard, Robin of Loxley wins the hand of Marian of Bagelle in marriage.

Rock All Night

Cloud Nine, the local teen hangout, has been taken over by a pair of escaped killers, who hold the local teens hostage. The bartender realizes it's up to him to save the kids.

Room 237

Stanley Kubrick's classic film, 'The Shining', gets a riveting and in-depth exploration of its hidden meanings, dazzling puzzles and even conspiracy theories.

Runaway Daughters�

3 teenagers are unable to adjust at home and in high-school. Tempted with an easy, carefree life they soon pass from misdemeanors into serious crime - and will suffer for it.

Rust Creek

A young woman trapped in a nightmare odyssey deep in the Kentucky woods must summon extraordinary courage in order to make it out alive in this harrowing survival thriller.

Ruthless Four, The

A group of men embark on a mission to discover a golden treasure from a mine.

The Saddest Music in the World

A woman announces a competition to determine the saddest music on earth. As musicians vie for the $25,000 prize, the world listens in on the radio.

Saga of the Viking Women

A group of lonely Viking women build a ship and set off across the sea to locate their missing menfolk, only to fall into the clutches of the barbarians that also hold their men captive.

Salvation, The

The mighty Mads Mikkelsen unleashes a maelstrom of bloodshed in the Wild West in this white-knuckle tale of revenge, co-starring Eva Green.

Save The Date

Lizzy Caplan & Alison Brie star in a romantic comedy about 2 very different sisters, and their adventures in love, lust and a race to the altar.

Seven Five, The

Meet the dirtiest cop in NYC history. Michael Dowd stole money and dealt drugs while patrolling the streets of 80s Brooklyn. He tells all in this explosive true crime saga.

Sexual Chronicles of a French Family

The life of a modern family is turned upside down when each of the adult family member's erotic adventures are captured on video, in this sexy drama.

Shadow

A gripping thriller about a US combat vet who finds himself the target of a band of deranged hunters.

Shake, Rattle & Rock

A group of concerned adults try to ban rock and roll music in their town because they think that the music promotes juvenile delinquency.

She Creature, The

A mysterious hypnotist reverts his beautiful assistant back into the form of a prehistoric sea monster that she was in a past life.

Sky

In this road trip odyssey, a woman (Diane Kruger) flees a failing marriage and finds passionate romance in the arms of a Las Vegas cowboy (Norman Reedus). With Lena Dunham.

Slow Learners

Embarrassingly unlucky at love, Jeff and Anne (Adam Pally and Sarah Burns) hatch a plan to transform themselves over the course of a sex and alcohol fueled summer.

Snowtown Murders, The

A charismatic serial murderer befriends a troubled teen and then slowly seduces him into a darkly violent and unforgiving new world.

Sorority Girl

A poor-little-rich-girl feels alienated by her mother and enacts a string of revenges on her fellow pupils at a girls' boarding school.

Spaceballs

BBC America Presents: The evil forces of Planet Spaceball attempt to poach Planet Druidia's fresh air supply, while Lone Starr and his friends fight to protect their planet's precious resource.

Stolen

Jon Hamm stars in this chilling mystery as a detective who discovers that the remains of a child could be linked to the serial killer who may have abducted his own son.

Submarine Seahawk

For his first command in the Pacific war an officer is ordered to take his submarine on a reconnaissance mission to locate a fleet of Japanese fighting ships the Allies have lost track of.

Submerged

In this breathless thriller, a group of friends fight to survive when their stretch limo is run off the road and under water by kidnappers, who then dive in to finish the job.

Suicide Battalion

During the Japanese invasion of the Philippines, an American commando team is sent to an evacuated American base in the jungle to destroy classified documents.

Summit, The

This film tells the thrilling story of the deadliest day on the world's most dangerous mountain, when 11 climbers mysteriously perished on K2.

Sweet Virginia

The Walking Dead's Jon Bernthal stars in this neo-noir crime thriller where a hitman and troubled small-town motel owner collide in an unsettling tale of sex and violence.

Sword of Trust

Marc Maron ("Glow") is a pawnshop owner set to cash-out when Cynthia (Jillian Bell) tries to hawk a Civil War relic sought after by local conspiracy theorists in this hilarious comedy.

Tale of Tales

Salma Hayek and John C. Reilly are Queen and King in this gory, gorgeous grown-up fairytale full of princes & princesses, sorcerers & fairies, and fearsome monsters & ogres.

Tank Commandos

A demolition squad searches for how the Germans are getting tanks across a river. An Italian boy leads them to a bridge under the surface of the water.

Terror Beneath the Sea

Two reporters discover that there is a race of fish-men living under the sea. The fish-men capture the pair and keep them prisoner in their underwater city.

That Summer

The inspiration for Documentary Now Season 1, Episode 1 "Sandy Passage": Welcome to GREY GARDENS...as you've never seen it before. Discover the long-lost film featuring Big and Little Edie before they were cultural icons. With Andy Warhol.

Total Recall (1990)

In 2084, Douglas Quaid opts for a false memory implant to experience a virtual vacation in Mars. When he realizes his entire life might be a false memory, he must visit Mars to find reality.

Trail of the Screaming Forehead

After a meteor crashes on an idyllic town, can anyone stop a band of rampaging alien foreheads as they suck the souls of the innocent and turn them into zombies?

Tribes of Palos Verdes, The

Jennifer Garner co-stars in this scathing exploration of the sex, drugs and secrets that lie just beneath the surface of a tranquil California beachfront paradise.

Trishna

Freida Pinto stars as a beautiful young woman who becomes the sexual pawn of her lover and is pushed to the breaking point.

Uncle Kent

In this hilarious erotic comedy, a fortysomething bachelor invites two sexy women home for the weekend and things get quickly out of control.

Undead, The

A beautiful woman is sent back in time via hypnosis to the Middle Ages where she finds she is suspected of being a witch, and subject to being executed.

Victim

In this haunting, twisted thriller, a rich surgeon and his brutal henchman kidnap a cop and transform him into a grotesque facsimile of the doctor's missing daughter.

Violent Midnight

A war veteran from a wealthy but troubled New England family is suspected in a series of brutal murders in his small town.

Voodoo Woman

Deep in the jungles a mad scientist is using the natives' voodoo for his experiments to create an indestructible being to serve his will.

Walking Out

Father and son fight to escape an unforgiving no man's land in this riveting survival thriller. Matt Bomer, Bill Pullman and Josh Wiggins star.

War of the Colossal Beast

Glenn Manning, "The Amazing Colossal Man," believed dead after falling from the Hoover Dam, reemerges in rural Mexico, brain damaged, disfigured, and very hungry.

War of the Fools

IFC Presents: Karel Zeman's brilliant animation, cowritten with Jurácek: ironic, surreal, following the adventures of a plowboy and a mercenary to the battlefields of the Thirty Years War.

Wedding Guest, The

Dev Patel stars as a man with a secret who is forced on the run across East Asia after kidnapping a bride to be in this noir thriller from director Michael Winterbottom.

Welcome to New York

Gérard Depardieu is a powerful, sex-obsessed French World Bank chief in this torn-from-the-headlines saga of sin and money based on actual events. Jacqueline Bisset co-stars.

Wet Asphalt

A young man of high principles has his illusions shattered when the journalist he respected resorts to publishing lies.

The Wind

The forces of nature tremble with an unseen evil in this chilling western tale of madness, paranoia and supernatural terror howling across the homestead.

xx/xy

A man finds himself having to decide between one of two women, not once, but twice. This drama stars Mark Ruffalo and was nominated for the Grand Jury Prize at Sundance.
